CONSTITUTION OF THE INNERSITE ASSOCIATION

Article I: Purpose
[cite_start]INNERSITE is established as a Decentralized Unincorporated Nonprofit Association (DUNA) to maintain a sovereign registry of human intent[cite: 137, 139].

Article II: The Logic of Three
All governance must adhere to the 3-6-9 logic framework. [cite_start]No action shall be taken that violates the "Zenith" (State 9) parameters established by the human anchor[cite: 1, 17, 18].

Article III: Equity
INNERSITE has no traditional equity. Ownership is expressed through 369 'Architect Keys.' [cite_start]Key holders provide 'Resonance Auditing' and receive protocol fees[cite: 24, 29].

Article IV: Sovereignty
The Association shall never claim ownership over user data. [cite_start]Users retain exclusive control of their private keys and fingerprints[cite: 49, 51].
